[DOCUMENT]
TITLE: Thread Scheduling
REQ_PREFIX: ZEP-SRS-2-

[GRAMMAR]
IMPORT_FROM_FILE: software_requirements.sgra

[TEXT]
STATEMENT: >>>
SPDX-License-Identifier: Apache-2.0
<<<

[[SECTION]]
TITLE: Thread Scheduling

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: ZEP-SRS-2-4
STATUS: Draft
TYPE: Functional
COMPONENT: Thread Scheduling
TITLE: Scheduling a thread based on an event
STATEMENT: >>>
When an event on which a thread is waiting occurs, the Zephyr RTOS shall make the waiting thread ready, so that it becomes eligible for selection by the scheduler.
<<<
USER_STORY: >>>
As a Zephyr RTOS user, I want to be able to execute work which reacts on events and interrupts the current executed work.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: ZEP-SYRS-15

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: ZEP-SRS-2-5
STATUS: Draft
TYPE: Functional
COMPONENT: Thread Scheduling
TITLE: Deadline Scheduling Priorities
STATEMENT: >>>
Where earliest-deadline-first scheduling is enabled, when two or more ready threads have equal static priority, the Zephyr RTOS shall consider the thread with the earliest deadline to have the higher priority.
<<<
USER_STORY: >>>
As a Zephyr RTOS user, I want to be able to schedule threads by earliest deadline first.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: ZEP-SYRS-17

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: ZEP-SRS-2-24
STATUS: Draft
TYPE: Functional
COMPONENT: Thread Scheduling
TITLE: Deadline scheduling tie-breaking
STATEMENT: >>>
Where earliest-deadline-first scheduling is enabled, when two or more ready threads have equal static priority and equal deadlines, the Zephyr RTOS shall treat them as threads of equal priority.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: ZEP-SYRS-17

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: ZEP-SRS-2-8
STATUS: Draft
TYPE: Functional
COMPONENT: Thread Scheduling
TITLE: Numeric thread priorities
STATEMENT: >>>
The Zephyr RTOS shall schedule threads according to a numeric thread priority, giving a thread with a numerically lower priority value precedence over a thread with a numerically higher priority value.
<<<
USER_STORY: >>>
As a Zephyr RTOS user, I want the OS to schedule threads by numeric priority so that I can control the relative importance of my threads.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: ZEP-SYRS-17

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: ZEP-SRS-2-9
STATUS: Draft
TYPE: Functional
COMPONENT: Thread Scheduling
TITLE: Preemption support
STATEMENT: >>>
While the current thread is preemptible, when a thread of higher priority becomes ready, the Zephyr RTOS shall suspend execution of the current thread and select the higher-priority thread as the current thread.
<<<
USER_STORY: >>>
As a Zephyr RTOS user, I want a higher priority thread to take over the CPU as soon as it becomes ready, so that important work is not delayed by less important work.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: ZEP-SYRS-17

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: ZEP-SRS-2-10
STATUS: Draft
TYPE: Functional
COMPONENT: Thread Scheduling
TITLE: Cooperative thread priorities
STATEMENT: >>>
The Zephyr RTOS shall support designating a range of thread priorities as cooperative, such that a thread executing at one of these priorities is not subject to preemption by other threads.
<<<
USER_STORY: >>>
As a Zephyr RTOS user, I want to be able to assign threads a priority that exempts them from preemption by other threads.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: ZEP-SYRS-17

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: ZEP-SRS-2-11
STATUS: Draft
TYPE: Functional
COMPONENT: Thread Scheduling
TITLE: Time sharing of CPU resources
STATEMENT: >>>
Where time slicing is enabled, the Zephyr RTOS shall cause the current preemptible thread to relinquish the CPU after not more than a configurable time slice period whenever one or more other ready threads of the same priority exist.
<<<
USER_STORY: >>>
As a Zephyr RTOS user, I want to be able to configure my RTOS in the way, that the CPU resources are shared evenly among executed threads of the same priority.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: ZEP-SYRS-16

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: ZEP-SRS-2-12
STATUS: Draft
TYPE: Functional
COMPONENT: Thread Scheduling
TITLE: Selecting the current thread
STATEMENT: >>>
When a scheduling decision is made on a CPU, the Zephyr RTOS shall select as the current thread the highest-priority ready thread that is eligible to execute on that CPU.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: ZEP-SYRS-16

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: ZEP-SRS-2-13
STATUS: Draft
TYPE: Functional
COMPONENT: Thread Scheduling
TITLE: Scheduling threads of equal priority
STATEMENT: >>>
When two or more ready threads share the same priority, the Zephyr RTOS shall select among them the thread that has been ready the longest.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: ZEP-SYRS-16

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: ZEP-SRS-2-14
STATUS: Draft
TYPE: Functional
COMPONENT: Thread Scheduling
TITLE: Cooperative threads
STATEMENT: >>>
The Zephyr RTOS shall support cooperative threads that, once running, remain the current thread until they yield or block.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: ZEP-SYRS-17

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: ZEP-SRS-2-15
STATUS: Draft
TYPE: Functional
COMPONENT: Thread Scheduling
TITLE: Yielding the CPU
STATEMENT: >>>
The Zephyr RTOS shall provide an interface for the current thread to voluntarily relinquish the CPU to other ready threads of the same or higher priority. If no ready thread of the same or higher priority exists, the current thread shall continue to execute.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: ZEP-SYRS-16

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: ZEP-SRS-2-16
STATUS: Draft
TYPE: Functional
COMPONENT: Thread Scheduling
TITLE: Locking the scheduler
STATEMENT: >>>
The Zephyr RTOS shall provide interfaces for a preemptible thread to disable preemption of itself by other threads and to subsequently restore its preemptible status.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: ZEP-SYRS-16

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: ZEP-SRS-2-25
STATUS: Draft
TYPE: Functional
COMPONENT: Thread Scheduling
TITLE: Blocking with the scheduler locked
STATEMENT: >>>
While a thread has disabled preemption, when that thread becomes unready, the Zephyr RTOS shall allow other threads to execute and shall maintain the thread's non-preemptible status when it becomes the current thread again.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: ZEP-SYRS-16

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: ZEP-SRS-2-17
STATUS: Draft
TYPE: Functional
COMPONENT: Thread Scheduling
TITLE: Setting a thread deadline
STATEMENT: >>>
Where earliest-deadline-first scheduling is enabled, the Zephyr RTOS shall provide an interface to set a thread's deadline.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: ZEP-SYRS-17

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: ZEP-SRS-2-18
STATUS: Draft
TYPE: Functional
COMPONENT: Thread Scheduling
TITLE: Per-thread time slice
STATEMENT: >>>
Where per-thread time slicing is enabled, the Zephyr RTOS shall provide an interface to set an individual time slice duration and expiry callback for a specific thread.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: ZEP-SYRS-16

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: ZEP-SRS-2-19
STATUS: Draft
TYPE: Functional
COMPONENT: Thread Scheduling
TITLE: Forcing a scheduling decision
STATEMENT: >>>
The Zephyr RTOS shall provide an interface to request an immediate re-evaluation of the scheduling decision on the current CPU in accordance with the scheduling rules. When invoked from an interrupt service routine, the re-evaluation shall occur upon exit from the interrupt.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: ZEP-SYRS-16

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: ZEP-SRS-2-20
STATUS: Draft
TYPE: Functional
COMPONENT: Thread Scheduling
TITLE: Querying thread preemptibility
STATEMENT: >>>
The Zephyr RTOS shall provide an interface to determine whether the currently executing context can be preempted.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: ZEP-SYRS-16

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: ZEP-SRS-2-21
STATUS: Draft
TYPE: Non-Functional
COMPONENT: Thread Scheduling
TITLE: Selecting the ready queue implementation
STATEMENT: >>>
The Zephyr RTOS shall support selecting the scheduler's ready queue implementation at build time, allowing the selection to trade off memory usage, code size, and scheduling performance as the number of ready threads grows.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: ZEP-SYRS-16

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: ZEP-SRS-2-22
STATUS: Draft
TYPE: Functional
COMPONENT: Thread Scheduling
TITLE: Meta-IRQ thread scheduling
STATEMENT: >>>
Where meta-IRQ priorities are configured, when a meta-IRQ thread becomes ready, the Zephyr RTOS shall preempt the current thread, including a cooperative or scheduler-locked thread or a lower-priority meta-IRQ thread, and select the meta-IRQ thread as the current thread. A running meta-IRQ thread shall remain interruptible by interrupt service routines.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: ZEP-SYRS-17

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: ZEP-SRS-2-23
STATUS: Draft
TYPE: Functional
COMPONENT: Thread Scheduling
TITLE: Time slice priority threshold
STATEMENT: >>>
Where time slicing is enabled, the Zephyr RTOS shall exempt threads whose priority is higher than a configurable priority threshold from time slicing.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: ZEP-SRS-2-11

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: ZEP-SRS-2-26
STATUS: Draft
TYPE: Functional
COMPONENT: Thread Scheduling
TITLE: Thread sleeping
STATEMENT: >>>
The Zephyr RTOS shall provide an interface for the current thread to suspend its own execution for a specified time period, relinquishing the CPU to other ready threads; when the period elapses, the thread shall become ready again.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: ZEP-SYRS-16

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: ZEP-SRS-2-27
STATUS: Draft
TYPE: Functional
COMPONENT: Thread Scheduling
TITLE: Waking a sleeping thread
STATEMENT: >>>
The Zephyr RTOS shall provide an interface to make a sleeping thread ready before its sleep period elapses. Waking a thread that is not sleeping shall have no effect.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: ZEP-SYRS-16

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: ZEP-SRS-2-28
STATUS: Draft
TYPE: Functional
COMPONENT: Thread Scheduling
TITLE: Busy waiting
STATEMENT: >>>
The Zephyr RTOS shall provide an interface for the current thread to delay its processing for a specified time period without relinquishing the CPU to other ready threads.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: ZEP-SYRS-16

[[/SECTION]]
